Paine now plays a good pull shot through the leg side for one.
Shorter and on off, TH plays it towards cover and a single is taken.
FOUR! Australia one short of 400 now! A full ball around off, Head loves it there, he creams it through covers for a boundary.
Another tossed up ball, it is played to the man at cover.
A single now as this is pushed towards cover. 400 up for the Aussies.
Gives it a lot of air and lands it on off, Paine strokes it through covers for one.
On middle, this is worked to the fielder at mid-wicket.
Outside off, not played at.
Bouncer! The batsman does well to evade it.
On the shorter side, Paine pulls it towards mid-wicket.
Another bouncer and another pull shot! To the man at short fine leg.
Paine comes down the track and Wagner bangs it short. Paine watches it go over him as he ducks under it. Strange from Paine there, not sure one would want to give Wagner the charge.
On the body, Paine looks to leave it but is hit on the body.
Pushed to the cover region by the batsman. They pick up a single.
Full and around middle, flicked towards short mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, driven straight to cover.
Outside off, turning away, short in length, punched through the covers for a single.
Short and outside off, punched straight to short extra cover.
Comes down the track but then Santner drops it short. Travis adjusts quickly, goes back and dabs it towards point for a quick single. The stand is now worth 120.
Full and down the leg side, Paine flicks it through square leg. A run taken.
A short one on middle, Paine ducks under it.
On the shorter side and on off, Paine keeps it out.
From around the wicket, he bangs it short, TP lets it go over him.
Back of a length and on off, Paine pushes it to covers.
On the bounce! One more short one, Paine takes on the challenge of pulling. He does not get on top of the bounce completely. It goes uppishly but well short of fine leg. One taken.
FOUR LEG BYES! A little too straight and slightly shorter. Head looks to flick but misses. It hits the pads and rolls down to the fine leg fence.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Loopy ball on off, Santner pushes it towards cover for one.
Quicker and just outside off, Head looks to cut but ends up chopping it on the off side.
On off, blocked.
Flatter and on off, TH keeps it out.
On middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Back of a length and on off, blocked.

Lovely shot down the ground! It deserved a boundary but the batters get two. Fuller and around off, Paine shows the full face of the bat and hits it through mid off. Williamson from that position tracks it down and saves two for his side.
On the shorter side, this is pulled on the leg side for one.
On off, defended.
Another delivery on the stumps, kept out.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Head looks to cut but that shot is not on. He ends up chopping it on the off side. TH wanted a run but is sent back.
Flatter and on middle, it is defended back to the bowler.
On middle, this is eased down to long on for one.
On the shorter side outside off, Head slaps it through covers for one.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
It is hit through covers for a single.

Fired on the pads, Head looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. There is an appeal from the bowler but the umpire shakes his head. Ball Tracker shows it would have clipped the leg pole. So it was a lot closer than we thought.
Angled into the pads, it is worked to mid on.
Outside off, let alone.
Close! On a length and around off, this is tapped towards the point fielder and the batters take off. Nicholls gets to the ball, picks it up and has a shy at the striker's end but misses.
Good ball and well played! A quick short ball and it is keeps rising. Head does well to hop and lower his arms to let it go.
Boult looks to follow the bumper with a yorker but ends up bowling a low full toss which Head dugs out towards mid on.
One more quick bumper, it gets Head hopping as he looks to fend it. The ball hits the higher part of the bat and lands on the off side. A good over comes to an end by Boult.
Very full and on off, this is squeezed out towards cover for one.
The arm ball outside off, Head looks to defend but does so inside the line, it goes off the outer half through short third man for two.
On off, TH goes back and keeps it out.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Slower through the air but shorter in length. Head slaps it through covers for one.
On middle, defended.
Full and fast swinging in, worked towards short mid-wicket.
On a length, around off, Head hops and pushes it towards mid on.
Full and outside off, swinging in, driven straight to short extra cover.
Around middle, angling in, turned towards deep backward square leg for a single.
WIDE! That is short but a bit too high. It is generated at good pace too, but Paine just watches it sail past, over his head. The stand is worth 140 now.
Outside off, dabbed straight to gully.

FOUR LEG BYES! Boult gets swing but loses his radar. Full in length, but down the leg side. Paine misses his flick but the ball goes off his pads, well wide of the diving Watling, to the fine leg fence.
Full on middle, Head comes down the track and pushes it towards long on for a single. Moves to 97.

Good awareness from Tim Paine. He sees that the Kiwis are a bit deep for him, as opposed to when Travis Head is on strike. Just works it through square leg, looks at Head and calls him through for a run.
Short and outside off Travis looks to cut but gets a bottom edge towards point.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
A touch short, TH gets across and nudges it to the leg side.
Short and outside off, punched through the covers for a run. Moves to 98. Got an over now, to try and get that century before Tea.
A length ball around middle, moving away, Head pokes it towards gully.

Ohhhh....opportunity missed. Boult gives a length ball on the pads and Travis Head has the full leg side part of the ground for his century. But he works it to the only man in front of square on the leg side - short mid-wicket!
Landed outside off, Travis dabs it towards gully where the fielder leaps to stop.
Full on middle, Head gets across and works it towards short mid-wicket.
Excellent work by Tom Latham! Full on off, Heads works it towards long on. Or, tries to. But cannot get past Tom Latham who dives to his right from short mid-wicket to stop it!
Boo!!!!!! goes the crowd. the break. Full and around off, Head just pushes it towards point. TEA ON DAY 2!
Full on middle, pushed through mid on for a single.
Moves to 99. Full and outside off, head presses this with soft hands towards cover and sets off for a run.
Full on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on but short mid-wicket intercepts.
Outside off, Paine drives it towards long off but Santner dives to his left to stop.
Turn and bounce there. Outside off, Tim initially looks to leave but then attempts to cut. Is beaten.
Full and outside off pushed towards cover for a quick single.

OUT! LBW! Wicket for Wagner but everyone looks surprised. That review seemed to be more out of desperation but it has struck gold. A length ball, outside off, Paine gets across to work it to the leg side but misses and is hit on the pads. Wagner appeals instantly but umpire Marais Erasmus does not react. Now, here is the interesting thing about the review. The men behind the stumps are not too keen about the referral but Wagner wants it. Williamson agrees and signals the 'T'. To the naked eye, the impact looks outside off and given that Paine has been hit on the knee roll, the height seems to be an issue as well. But here comes Ball Tracker. The impact is in line and the projection is shown to be hitting the stumps! Even Marais Erasmus is surprised by that. But Paine has to go after a wonderful knock. The 150-run stand has been broken at last.
Full and down the leg side, left alone.
There is the single. The crowd applauds, not for Starc getting off the mark but because Head gets back on strike. Full and down the leg side, tickled towards fine leg for a single.
Whoa! That is a good surprised ball. Wagner bowls a high full toss, which dips on its way towards the batsman. But Travis is watchful, sees the ball till the last moment and defends.
Full and outside off, stays low, Travis looks to punch but ends up chopping it on the bounce towards first slip. The fielder dives to his left to stop.
Misses out again! Full and around middle, flicked straight to square leg. Head stays on 99.

OUT! In the air... taken! Starc fails to make an impact. He was sent to score some quick runs but falls in the attempt to do so. Southee bowls a slower one, it is fuller in length. Starc looks to go over mid off but fails to get the correct connection. Williamson takes an easy catch. Two wickets in two overs for the Kiwis.
Full and very wide outside off, left alone.

FOUR! 100 for Travis Head! Takes his helmet off and raises both his hands one holding the helmet and the other the bat. The crowd is up on its feet and so are his teammates applauding the knock. It is his second in this format. A very patient innings by him. He gets a gift to get there. Full and wide outside off, Head squeezes it through point and bags a boundary. We will now probably see him change gears here.
Back of a length and on off, Head guides it towards point for one.
Full and wide outside off, Pattinson goes after it but misses.
FOUR! Lovely shot to get off the mark! It is just behind a driving length around off, Pattinson creams it through covers. Latham gives it a chase and also puts in a dive but his effort goes in vain.

NOT OUT! Umpire's call it is! That was very close. It could have gone either way to be honest. Wagner runs in and lands it on middle, Head shuffles right across and looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards fine leg as the batters run two. The bowler in the meantime makes a huge appeal but it is turned down. After a discussion, the Kiwi players review. Replays roll in and it shows the ball to be clipping the top of middle and leg. New Zealand do not lose their review. The umpire after everything signals leg byes.
A lovely follow-up. Head backs away to the leg side and Wagner follows him with a yorker on leg stump. Head just about gets his bat down on time to push it towards mid on.
Full on middle, driven straight to mid on.
A bouncer, right at the head of Travis, he just about ducks in time.
FOUR! Nicely played! A short one and on off, Head plays the upper cut. It goes very fine on the off side for a boundary. 450 up for Australia.
FOUR! Crunched! Back-to-back boundaries! Head clears his front leg and this is bowled full and on middle, it is hammered through covers for another boundary. 10 from the over.
On the pads, it is worked towards fine leg for one.
On the shorter side outside off, Head cuts it behind point. The fielder in the deep runs to his right and makes a diving stop. Only the one taken.
A muted appeal! This is angled into the batter. Pattinson keeps it out with his bat and pad close to each other. Southee appeals as he feels it is pad first but nothing from the umpire.
Fuller and on off, this is hit down to long off for one.
On the shorter side, closer to the body of Head. He looks to upper cut it but misses.
Another short one, Head pulls it hard but very close to the fielder at mid-wicket. A single taken.
A yorker on the stumps, Head squeezes it out towards point.

OUT! CAUGHT! Wagner gets his fourth. However, the first thing he does is after picking a wicket is walks upto Head and shakes his hand. Now all the Kiwi players do so. Head walks off to a standing ovation from the crowd. End of an excellent innings from him. He too falls in the attempt to score some quick runs. He makes room again and Wagner bowls a full toss. He looks to go big but ends up splicing it towards cover where Santner takes an easy catch. Australia though continue to bat on.
On the fuller side, Cummins strokes it to covers.

Confusion but safe! On a length and around off, Cummins strokes it towards Williamson at covers. He misfields. Cummins wants a run but is sent back. Rightly so as had they gone for it, it would have been very risky.
A short one now, Cummins looks to play the upper cut but does not connect.
A full toss on middle, it is worked towards mid-wicket. A wicket maiden for Wagner.
FOUR! Up and over! Tim Southee has now gone for 100 runs. A short one on middle, Pattinson pulls it over mid-wicket. No one in the deep so a boundary results.
Southee lands this on a length and outside off, Pattinson plays it late through point for one.

OUT! Taken! Cummins bags a duck! Another batter dismissed off a full toss. Southee bowls a slower one, it is a low full toss. Cummins is a touch early in the flick and hence, it goes uppishly towards mid-wicket. Latham there times his jump and takes a good catch with both his hand stretched upwards.
On off, Lyon blocks it nicely.
Back of a length and on off, Lyon keeps it out.
On the stumps, NL plays it towards mid on.
A yorker on middle, Pattinson does well to jam it out.
A full toss on middle, Pattinson works it through mid-wicket for one.
On the fuller side on off, Lyon strokes it to covers.
On the pads, it is flicked through square leg for one.
A short one on middle, Pattinson ducks under it.
Misfield and two! A slower one, fuller outside off, Pattinson strokes it towards cover where the fielder does not stop it. Two taken.

OUT! Wagner takes the catch! No fifer for him but AUSTRALIA HAVE BEEN BOWLED OUT FOR 467! A short one on middle, Lyon pulls it nicely, but it does not have the power behind it to clear the long boundaries here. It goes towards fine leg where Wagner takes a good catch.

No ball! So the wait continues for Australia to bowl their first legal delivery in this game. Latham is also off the mark. It is a length ball around middle, Latham pushes it towards mid on and takes off. The fielder picks the ball up and has a shy at the striker's end but misses. Also, that is a big no ball by Starc. He may have missed his run-up.
Back of a length and on off, it is guided to gully.
A huge appeal from the slip cordon but nothing from the bowler! This is full and on off, Blundell looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On the pads, Blundell is off the mark now as he works it through mid-wicket and takes two.
Another couple! This is fuller again and on middle, Blundell works it past square leg and takes two more.
Two leg byes now! A little bit of movement for Starc. Inward movement. The line is very straight though. Blundell looks to flick but misses. It hits the pads and rolls on the leg side. Two taken.

BEATEN! That was quick. That even took Paine aback as he collected the ball. It is full and around off, Blundell is beaten for pace as he looks to drive. Paine collects it in front of his face and almost loses balance.

In the air... but safe! That was right off the glove! A short one and on the body. Latham looks to work it on the leg side but fails to get on top of the bounce. It hits the glove and lobs behind but lands short of the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.
On the off stump, Latham is solid in defense.
Outside off again, it is not played at. The Australian bowlers haven't got the same movement as the Kiwi bowlers.
One more ball outside off, Latham shoulders arms to this one.
BEATEN! Very full and outside off, Latham goes for a booming drive but is beaten. The length was not quite right to play the drive.
Outside off, looking to curl it back in. It does not. Easy leave for the batter.
Very full and straight, Blundell mistimes his drive back to the bowler. That was delivered at 148.7 KPH. Starc is really bowling quick here.

FOUR! That is a lovely shot by Blundell! It is shorter this time and outside off, Blundell gets on top of the bounce and guides it through point for a boundary. First of the game and it is a quality shot. A back foot punch to someone of Starc's pace is not easy.

FOUR BYES! That has taken off out of nowhere! It is a length delivery outside off, Blundell lets it be. It keeps rising after going past the batter. Paine hops but fails to collect it and it goes to the fence behind.
Still no movement! On a length and on off, Blundell keeps it out.

FOUR! This is a positive start for the Kiwis! Another boundary. On the pads, it is flicked fine on the leg side and the ball races away to the fence. Three boundaries in this over. 12 from it in total.
Back of a length and on off, kept out.
On the fuller side and on middle, Latham keeps it out nicely.
A good bumper, Latham sways out of the way at the very end.
Outside off, it is left alone.
One more delivery outside off, Latham does not fiddle with it.
An ambitious appeal! This lands on middle and then jags back in. Latham looks to keep it out but misses to get hit high on the pads. An appeal but it is too high.

Very good awareness from Tom Blundell. Before this ball, Starc had two men deep on the leg side for him. But Tom expected that this might be a double bluff. And it was. Mitchell bowled it at pace, 145.7 kph, probably expecting Blundell to play at that. But Tom let it through.
Landed outside off, let through again.
Nice shot. A length ball outside off, extra bounce but TB rises with the bounce and plays it beautifully, placing it between gully and backward point. Three runs taken.
Down the leg side, Latham misses his flick.
Another one in the 140s, watchfully defended.
Around off, pushed towards point.
Outside off, not played at.
Shorter in length and outside off, Blundell looks to push it through the off side but it goes off the underedge and on the bounce to second slip.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Pat Cummins draws first blood and Blundell's return into the team is not a good one. Cummins goes full and around off, it is not a driving length delivery. The ball holds its line a touch. Blundell goes for the drive but the ball goes off the outside edge and to Paine who makes no mistake. Early wicket for Australia. New Zealand trail by 444 runs.
Outside off, left alone.

Williamson's away! He opens the face of his bat on this length delivery and guides it through backward point. They take two quickly and go for the third. Complete it. Good running. End of a successful over for Australia.
Full and outside off, Williamson shoulders arms to it. Good carry to the keeper.
Just short! Williamson goes after this full and very wide delivery. It goes off the outer half but lands just short of Warner at gully.
A good bumper, Williamson spots it early and evades it.
Another bumper! Williamson ducks under it again. This though is signaled as a wide for height.
Top class stuff from Starc! After two bumpers he bowls a yorker now on off, Williamson is up for the challenge as he jams it out.
Goes back to bowling it short. Williamson does not play at it.
Length to end on off, Williamson is solid in defense.
Cummins comes from aroundthe wicket to the left-hander. He bowls it on off, Latham keeps it out nicely.
Back of a length and on off, Latham keeps it out off the back foot.
Angles it into the off pole, Latham keeps it out nicely. Cummins is hoping one ball to straighten after pitching. That has not happened yet.
Slightly shorter and around off, Latham leaves it on length.
That cuts him into half! What a delivery. It lands outside off and Latham looks to defend. He leaves a gap between bat and pad. The ball jags back and sneaks through that gap.
Outside off, Latham shoulders arms to this one.
Shorter and on off, Williamson guides it to point.
Another back of a length delivery, Williamson plays it late again and gets it through backward point for one.
Just outside off, Latham makes a good leave.
On the pads, Tom Latham works it to mid-wicket.
Another delivery on a length and on off, Latham prods forward and blocks it solidly.
On the pads, Latham looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Pattinson is appealing but he is the only one doing so. The ball rolls on the leg side. A leg bye is taken.
A bit of a loose drive that from Latham. It is fuller in length. He plays it ahead of his body and hence, it is not timed well. Still goes through covers for two.
Outside off, not played at.
Another ball outside off, it is not played at.

Looks to bowl the yorker but ends up bowling a full toss down the leg side. It does take Latham by surprise as he tries to flick but is late on the shot. Had it been on target, it could have been a wicket.
A length delivery around off, Latham once again leaves it on length.
Once again cuts him into half! A good nut to end a  good over. On a length and outside off, it jags back in sharply. Goes between the gap of bat and pad as Latham tries to block it.
This is angled into the batter, Williamson looks to defend but it goes off the inner half through mid-wicket for one.
A short one on middle, Latham ducks under it.
On the pads, Latham looks to flick but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
Another back of a length delivery on off. Latham looks to keep it out but gets an inside edge onto the body.
On the shorter side, Latham gets on top of the bounce and pulls it through backward square leg for one.
Too high! Slightly shorter and around off, it jags back in. Williamson looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit high on the pads.
On the fuller side, Latham just puts bat to ball and strokes it through cover-point for two.
This is angled into the off pole. Latham stays back and keeps it out.
Another appeal but it is going down leg! Cummins angles this into the pads. Latham looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. A huge shout but nothing from the umpire.
Extra bounce and extra zip! Shorter around off, it skids through and also takes off after pitching. Latham does well to bail out of the defensive stroke.
BEATEN! Lovely nut again! Angles it into the off pole and then gets it to straighten right at the end. The ball whizzes past the outside edge.
One more ball outside off, Latham does not fiddle with it.

FOUR RUNNING RUNS! Seen that done by the Australian batters and now the Kiwi batsmen do so. A full ball outside off, there is a hint of away movement on that delivery. Williamson leans into the stroke and hits it through covers. The ball slows down as it gets to the ropes. Lyon hares after it from point and by the time he chases it down. The batters run four.

OUT! In the air... taken! Huge, huge wicket and the Australians know it. Their celebration says it all. Williamson has played a false stroke, just what New Zealand did not want. The Kiwi supporters are shocked. It is a short ball around off, Williamson looks to drag his pull but ends up getting a top edge as there is steep bounce on it. It goes high on the leg side. Paine runs after it, settles under it and takes a good catch. Another low score for Williamson.
A yorker now, Latham jams it out.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Outside off, it is left alone.

That is a beauty! The change of angle almost does the trick. Comes around the wicket and lands it on off, it straightens after pitching. Latham looks to defend but is beaten. End of a lovely over by Pattinson. He also got the big wicket of Williamson.
Good length and on off, defended.
Taylor is off the mark! He pushes this short ball wide of mid off and gets to the other end.

OUCH! That must have hurt. Slightly shorter and outside off, it jags back in sharply. Latham looks to leave but does not account for the movement. He gets hit on the bicep first and then on the chest.
On the pads, the batter looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.
On a length and around off, it straightens again. Beats the outside edge again. This is testing times for Latham. He needs to show a lot of character and fight out of this period.
On middle, Latham keeps it out nicely.

Dropped! Difficult to call that one though, he needed to react really quickly. It is angled into the pads of Taylor. He flicks it right off the middle. It hits the leg of Wade. He got no time to react there.

NOT OUT! That is going over! Did not see that coming. Excellent review by Taylor and the crowd erupts. Not sure if the game is being played in New Zealand or Australia. Pattinson steams in and angles it into the middle pole. Taylor plants his front foot way too across and tries to flick but misses. It hits the pad and a confident appeal is made. Up goes the finger. Taylor reviews immediately. Replays roll in and they show that the ball is going over. The Kiwi fans and players will breathe a huge sigh of relief.
Goes for a yorker but slips it down the leg side. Taylor misses the flick.
This is angled into the pads, Taylor is a touch late in the shot. He ends up pushing it back to the bowler.
Back of a length and on off, it is kept out.
A short ball on middle, Taylor ducks under it.

An edge straightaway! Yes, there is turn and bounce. Full and around off, Latham looks to defend but the ball spins away, bounces and takes the outside edge. But well wide of Steven Smith at first slip. A single taken.
Full and outside off, watchfully defended.
Around middle, worked towards short leg.
Full and outside off, driven straight back to the bowler.
Around off, watchfully blocked out.
Outside off, full and going straight on, let through.
A low full toss on off, Latham strokes it to covers.
Outside off, it is not played at.
One more delivery outside off, Latham does not fiddle with it.
This is angled into the batsman, Latham works it through square leg and takes two.
Outside off, Latham shoulders arms to this one.
One more ball outside off, Latham does not fiddle with it.
Floats it up on off, Taylor works it towards square leg for nothing.
This lands outside off and it turns back in. Taylor shuffles across and looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Flatter and outside off, it turns back in. Taylor works it to square leg.
Good amount of turn for Lyon there! It lands on off and comes back in. It works it to square leg.
On middle, Taylor works it to mid-wicket.
Tosses it up outside off, Taylor strokes it through covers for a single. A run from the last ball! THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 2!
Uppish but short! On a length and around off, Taylor looks to keep it out but does so with hard hands. It goes uppishly but well short of short extra cover.
Fuller in length and on middle, Taylor strokes it back to the bowler.
Lands another one on a length and around off, Taylor once again is solid in defense.
First run for today! Slightly fuller on middle, Taylor works it through mid-wicket for one.

That is a beauty! He angles it in from wide of the crease from around the wicket. Lands it on off, Latham looks to defend but it straightens and then whizzes past the outside edge. Not a lot you can do there but just hope it misses the outside edge.

'Definitely two noises' says Wade at short leg but Paine does not review. Great decision to not review as replay shows that there is no bat involved. Cummins this time angles it into the middle pole. It lands just behind a length. Latham looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the front pad. The ball lobs towards gully where Warner dives forward and takes it. A huge appeal but the umpire is unmoved. There is a discussion between the Australians but they do not review. Rightly so as replays show there is not bat and Ball Tracker shows it to be going over. End of a testing first over by Cummins.
Slightly shorter and on middle, it jags back in. Taylor looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Lovely delivery! The last time it came back in and this one goes away. It lands around middle and it is on a length. Taylor looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pads.
BEATEN! Beauty again. This lands on off, it pitches and moves away again. Taylor defends the original trajectory but the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
Pattinson is getting the ball to move both ways! Angles it in this time, Taylor works it down to fine leg and gets to the other end.
On middle, blocked.
Poke and beaten! Shorter in length and on off, it angles away. Latham looks to push at it away from the body but gets beaten. Two good overs to begin with by Australia.

OUT! Edged, dropped, no it has been taken! Taylor is out of here. This was coming. Australia have been on the money right from the first ball this morning and they have their first scalp of the day. Cummins bowls this fuller and around off, it straightens a touch. Taylor pushes at it with hard hands. It goes off the outside edge. It goes quickly towards Labuschagne at third slip who is quite low in his stance. He stretches his arms upwards to take the catch but fails to hang on. The ball though pops up just behind first slip. Burns is alert to that, he moves towards the ball and takes it. The Australians are delighted. Early wicket for them, just the start they would have wanted.

OUT! Umpire's call! It is clipping the top of leg pole! Cummins has two in two and Nicholls bags a first-baller. A horrible start this for Kiwis. They have lost two wickets in the 14 balls bowled today and they are staring down the barrel now. Cummins from around the wicket bowls it full and on the stumps. Nicholls shuffles right across and misses the flick shot. He is hit flush on the front pad right in front of the stumps. A huge shout and up goes the finger. HN reviews. Replays roll in and they show that the on-field call is the right one. JUST ABOUT. Because the impact is in line but the angle is taking the ball down the leg side, clipping the leg stump on height as per Ball Tracker! Nicholls trudges back, New Zealand do not lose a review though. Cummins is on a hat-trick for the 8TH TIME in his Test career.
No hat-trick. Watchfully negotiated. Good ball though. It is on middle, Watling lunges and keeps it out nicely.
Another one on middle, Watling is solid in defense.
WIDE! Way too short and it goes well over the batter who ducks under it.

FOUR! First shot of authority by a Kiwi batter today! It is full and around off, Watling leans into it and strokes it down to the long off fence. A good shot to get off the mark. Should give him a lot of confidence. 50 UP FOR NEW ZEALAND.
Cummins now goes wide and outside off, not played at. What an over by Cummins, two wickets in it. New Zealand still 416 runs away.

There is no respite for the Kiwi batters! Cummins just bowled an amazing over and now Pattinson starts the other with a beauty! It lands on off and on a length and then moves away. Latham does nothing wrong as he looks to defend the original trajectory but is beaten.

EDGED AND DROPPED! Steven Smith is the culprit. He probably should have just let the first slip fielder take it as it was straight to him. This is on a fuller length and around off, Latham looks to drive but does so inside the line. It flies off the outside edge between first and the second slip fielders. It is a lot closer to the former than the latter. Smith though dives to his right and looks to take it but fails to hang on. It goes towards third man for one. That would have been dreadful for New Zealand. Latham would want to make this count now. Also, you have to feel bad for Pattinson, he could have easily had three wickets by now but only has one.
On the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
On the fuller side on middle, Latham works it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off, not played at. End of an over which could have seen another wicket fall but that is not the case. Still a top over this.
Good shot! On the fuller side around off, Watling strokes it nicely but finds mid off.
Length delivery and outside off, it is left alone.
Good leave! This is in the 5th stump channel. Watling knows where his off pole is and lets it go through to the keeper.
A couple now! Off the outer half though. Fuller in length and around off, Latham looks to drive but the bat turns in his hands. It goes off the outer half through covers for two.
Lovely delivery! On a length and around off, gets it to straighten after pitching. Watling looks to defend but the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
Solid shot but for no runs! On the fuller side again, Watling plants his front foot forward and hits it nicely to mid off.
On the off pole, Latham keeps it out.
A nice short one by Pattinson! Latham looks to defend but there is extra bounce on this one. It hits the glove and luckily for Latham, it falls on the ground.
Just outside off, not played at.
Back of a length and on off, Latham pushes it towards mid off.
Loose stroke! Not sure that is the right shot by Latham, especially since he edged one early on. This is not that full and it is outside off, Latham goes after it but gets beaten.
Good shot for one! Slightly fuller again, Latham just puts bat to ball and gets it past mid off for one.
Drop and run! Shorter in length and on off, Latham plays it towards cover for one.
Outside off, it is left alone.

Just short! That seemed a late decision by Watling to play at it. It is shorter in length and on the body. It seemed like Watling initially looked to move out of the way but then tries to fend at it. It goes off something towards third slip but lands short of Labuschagne who dives forward to take it. Replays later on show that it was off the shoulder.

OHHH! Cummins seems like taking a wicket on every ball he bowls. This is on off, it is on a length. It skids through. Watling looks to defend but gets an inside edge which bounces behind the batter and then on the leg side. Watling though was alert to kick it away had it been rolling towards the stumps.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Just outside off and Watling does not play at it. Another excellent over by Cummins. 9 in his 4 overs today and 2 wickets for him.

Full and outside off, Latham pushes it through the covers and takes a single. Both batsmen return for the second but after taking a couple of steps, Latham stops and sends Watling back, as he feels he would not have made it in time. BJ has to apply the brakes and then go back. Gets back in time.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! This is a brute of a ball. Just cannot help remembering Ian Chappell time and time again. If he was on air, he would have definitely said - 'Had the batsmen run two, Watling would not have been out, because he would not have been on strike!' But a terrific ball from Patto. He has been steaming in from yesterday, desperate to make his presence felt and he gets his second scalp. This is absolutely unplayable. Pattinson bends his back and lands this back of a length outside off. BJ is forced to play at it but suddenly, the ball kicks off. It keeps on rising and takes the glove, lobbing to Joe Burns at first slip. 3/12 in 32 balls this morning.
Down the leg side, helped through square leg for a single to get off the mark.

A short ball, around off, Latham gets on top of the bounce and pulls it all along the ground through mid-wicket. The batsmen take two and then one more on the throw. De Grandhomme is a bit slow off the blocks but makes it in time.
A length ball outside off, Colin wants to have a feel of it, plays at it away from his body and misses.
A length ball but a bit too straight, CdG looks to flick but misses and is hit on the pads. A fiery over from Patto.
Just outside off, left alone.
On off, Latham lunges and keeps it out.
A bumper, Latham lets it go over him.
On the middle stump, Latham manages to block it out nicely.
Punched off the back foot by the batsman.

Good stop! This is angled into the batter and then Cummins gets it to hold its line. Latham looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards gully where the fielder dives to his right and stops it.
Slashes but misses! Outside off and shorter in length. Colin throws his bat at it but is beaten.
In the air... safe! This is angled into the pads. Colin looks to put bat to ball but it hits the face of the bat. Goes uppishly but well short of mid on.
De Grandhomme works it with the angle through square leg for one.
Just outside off, not played at.
Another one outside off, Latham shoulders arms to this one.
That was left on length! It was slightly shorter and around off, jags back in. Latham leaves it and it goes over the stumps.
Down the leg side to begin, a loosener. Colin looks to flick but misses.
Some inswing for Starc but the line is a little too straight. He looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
On middle, de Grandhomme pushes it to mid on.
Inside edge saves Colin! This is full and on middle, de Grandhomme looks to flick but gets an inside edge on the pads.
Nice shot! This time gets the flick shot right off the middle but to the man at mid on.
Around off, de Grandhomme guides it to point.
On the shorter side, Latham guides it through point for one.
Slightly shorter and on off, Colin is hurried into the pull shot. It goes towards wide mid on for one.

NO BALL AND FOUR! Played that late! It is shorter and outside off, Latham waits for it and guides it through backward point. The fielder in the deep runs to his right and dives but in vain. Wade has also overstepped.
Follows the boundary with a single as this is worked towards mid-wicket.
Fuller and on middle, Grandhomme strokes it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Second boundary in the over. Easy pickings for Colin de Grandhomme. A full toss wide outside off, Colin just guides it through backward point and it races away to the fence.
On the pads, de Grandhomme works it towards mid on for one. A pressure relieving over from Wade. He concedes 13, while his fast bowlers had conceded just 19 in 11 overs this morning.

Oops! Almost a run out! Excellent stuff from Matthew Wade. Around middle, de Grandhomme tucks it through the leg side. By reflex, he is out of his crease, looking for that single. But by that same reflex, Wade is quick to stop the ball at short leg. He collects and releases the ball quickly, at the striker's end but misses. Waiting for the replay to show where was CdG when the throw was fired.
A length ball, swinging in, Colin looks to flick but misses and is hit on the pads.
Outside off, played straight to Nathan Lyon at backward point.
Loose. Outside off, de Grandhomme looks to steer it to third man but does not bother moving his feet. Is beaten.
Lift off the surface. Fuller, outside off, Colin has a poke but the ball rises off the deck and beats his attempt.
A hat-trick of plays and misses! Outside off, on a length, slightly slower in pace, Colin pushes but misses.
FOUR! No one down there and a boundary! A loosener to begin with. Down the leg side, Latham sweeps it fine on the leg side and bags a boundary.
On middle, it is on the shorter side. Latham stays back and works it to short leg.
An appeal but just in hope! Latham comes down the track and looks to flick but misses the full toss. He is hit on the boot. An appeal but not given.
Flatter and on off, Latham stays back and keeps it out.
On off, Latham once again goes back and keeps it out.
Loopy ball on the off pole, Tom lunges forward and defends it onto the ground.
Full and on the pads, Colin de Grandhomme works it through square leg for one. It is a no ball as Starc overstepped.
The batsman has punched the ball off the back foot.
Back of a length and on off, Latham works it to mid on.

Overthrow! On middle, Latham looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards short leg. Wade there fumbles, he spots Latham did move out of his crease for a second so has a shy at the stumps. Misses, no one backing up and the batters take two. Starc's not happy but can't blame Wade to have a shy. Wouldn't have mattered had he hit though as Latham did get back in.
Outside off, left alone.

Direct hit and Colin de Grandhomme is a goner! Back of a length and on off, Latham drops it towards point and takes off. It is a risky run. Lyon picks the ball up and has a shy at the striker's end but misses. Colin was too casual there, he maybe thought that Lyon would go for the bowler's end and not his end.
On off, kept out.
Full on middle, Latham comes down the track and works it through mid-wicket for a single.
Around off, watchfully defended.
Down the leg side, helped throughb square leg for a run.
Outside off, eased through the covers for one.
Full and around off, Colin looks to flick, plays it a bit uppishly but it does it carry to short mid-wicket.
Outside off, de Grandhomme defends watchfully.
On the shorter side outside off, Latham lets it go to the keeper.
Another short ball and on the body, Latham once again lets it go over him.
Outside off, not played at.
On middle, Latham stays back and keeps it out nicely.
Outside off, not fiddled at.
On the pads, it is worked down to fine leg for one.
Top nut! Flatter and on off, maybe Latham should have played this on the front foot but he goes back and looks to keep it out. Gets beaten as it turns away.

FOUR! Lovely use of the feet and it is hit brilliantly. Latham comes down the track and gets to the pitch of the ball. Drives it through mid on for a boundary. Excellent shot as it was against the turn.
Three now! Slightly shorter this time and width on offer. Latham stays back and guides it through backward point for three.
Quicker on off, it turns back in. Colin keeps it out.
Loopy ball outside off, it turns back in. De Grandhomme works it with the turn to mid-wicket.

In the air... short! Colin de Grandhomme looks to go big. He also tries to play it with the turn. Tries to whip a ball from outside off. It is not off the middle though and hence, lands well short of the deep mid-wicket fielder. One taken.

OUT! TAKEN! There goes number six and now Starc is amongst the wickets. The budding stand has been cut short. This is on a length and around off, it is angling away. Colin de Grandhomme looks to defend but it goes off the shoulder of the bat towards gully where Warner takes it. Around 25 minutes to go before Lunch, can we see the Kiwis being bundled out?
Outside off, not played at.

NOT OUT! No conclusive evidence to overturn that and it remains not out. That could have gone either way to be honest. Paine has a chat with the umpire and rightly so, replays did suggest that it brushed the wrist band which is a part of the glove but the third umpire feels different. It is a short one and on the body. Santner looks to fend it by taking his eyes off the ball. It goes off some part of the arm towards Head at leg gully. He takes it and there is an appeal. The umpire shakes his head. After a discussion between short leg, silly point and the keeper, Paine reviews. Quite a few replays have been watched. It seems to indicate that the ball has hit the wrist band. However, Aleem Dar gives it in the favor of the batter. It was a tough decision so can't blame the umpire there. Australia lose a review.
One more bouncer, this time it is ducked under.
Another bumper, Santner lets it go to the keeper.
This is angled into the pads, Santner works it to mid-wicket.
Full and around off, Latham lunges and defends.
Full on middle, Tom comes down the track and looks to flick but gets a leading edge. Does not carry to cover.
Comes down the track, takes the ball on the full and flicks it towards short fine leg.
Short and outside off, punched through the covers for a couple.
Fractionally shorter than full, outside off, left alone.
That is a better length but not a great line. Much fuller from Lyon, inviting the drive but too wide outside off. Left alone.
Shorter and on the pads, Santner works it through square leg for one. 100 up for the visitors.
Back of a length and on off, Latham stands tall and keeps it out.
Shortish again, Latham hops and works it to short leg.
Slips this one down the leg side, it is left alone.
Shorter in length and outside off, Latham evades it.
Back of a length and on middle, Latham stays back and keeps it out nicely.
Floats it up on middle, Santner keeps it out.
Gives it a lot of air and lands it on off, blocked.
On middle, Santner comes forward and keeps it out.
BEATEN! Lyon lands it in a length where Santner is not sure whether to come forward or stay back. He gets it to turn away a little. Santner looks to defend staying rooted to his crease. Gets beaten.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Slower through the air this time and lands it on off, blocked.
Outside off, it is not played at.
A rib-tickler. Latham looks to flick but misses. It hits the thigh pad and rolls towards fine leg for one.
On the shorter side again, Santner stands tall and keeps it out.
Well played! A short one again, Santner does well to drop his hands and let it go to the keeper.
One more short one but down the leg side, left alone.
Ouch! That will hurt! Fractionally short and on the body, Santner again drops his hand but fails to move out of the way. The ball hits him on his bicep.
Flatter and around off, Latham guides it to point.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Latham comes down the track but does not get to the pitch of the ball. It is played to mid on.
Turn and bounce! Flatter on off, Latham goes back and tries to defend but the ball turns away and there is also extra bounce. Latham goes back and tries to defend but is beaten.
Slower through the air on middle, kept out.

Latham uses his feet again, he does not get to the pitch of it. Latham tries to defend but the ball hits the pad, then the bat and goes towards cover for one. There is an appeal by the keeper but nothing. A single to end the session. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3!
EDGED, FOUR! Fortuitous start for Latham after the break! Full and outside off, Tom looks to defend but the ball zips back in, takes the inside edge and goes past the stumps to the fine leg fence!
Full and just around off, watchfully defended.
Outside off, solidly defended.
A bouncer now, but down the leg side, comfortably ducked under.
Down the leg side, tucked towards fine leg for a single.

Is that a wicket? Not according to Marais Erasmus. There was a noise as the ball went past the bat. Tim Paine looks confident. The slips come charging towards the umpire. Paine has a chat with his bowler. Cummins is not sure. Eventually, no review taken. Full and outside off, coming in with the angle from around the wicket, Santner looked to defend but missed. There seemed to be a sound once the ball went past. Ultra Edge detects it coming off the pad. Top decision.
Around off, defended watchfully.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

16TH TEST FIFTY FOR LATHAM! It has been an excellent batting display against a world class bowling attack. He has taken a lot of time, 135 balls, to get to this landmark, which is also his third slowest half century but he will not care. He was given a life this morning but only Steven Smith would be remembering that now. Gets to his half century with a squeeze behind point. Three runs taken. The deficit is now 357.
Around off, defended watchfully.
Full and around off, Mitchell looks to defend but the ball goes off the inner half of the bat towards mid on.
That is a jaffa. On a length outside off, MS looks to block but the ball pitches and then straightens to beat the outside edge.
A length ball outside off, shouldered arms to.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through again.
A touch short outside off, Tom looks to tap and run to the off side but aborts the thought as Cummins gets to the ball quickly.
EDGED, SHORT! More luck for Latham. Full and outside off, TL looks to defend but the ball moves away and takes the outside edge. Falls short of a diving Marnus Labuschagne at third slip.
A bouncer now, Latham ducks.
Full and wide outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, Santner drives it straight to point.
Full and around off, Santner looks to defend but gets a thick inside edge onto his box.
On a good length outside off, Mitchell looks to defend but the ball lands and then seams away off the deck to beat the outside edge.
Full and fast, around middle, pushed towards mid on
A bouncer now, on middle, MS ducks.

Good running. On a length around off, Santner plays that with an open bat-face, getting it past David Warner at gully. Warner runs after it, gets to the ball, slides and then returns a good throw to the keeper but Santner is quick to come back for the second. Direct hit might have been interesting though.
On a good length and around off, Latham confidently strokes it to mid off.
Continues landing it on a length and around off, Latham is solid in defense again.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Latham does not last for long after the break and New Zealand are 7 down now. A loose stroke from Tom, he fails to continue after getting to his half ton. It is slightly fuller and outside off. Latham goes after it away from his body. He has been beaten twice or thrice playing this shot but this time it takes the edge and goes to the keeper who makes no mistake. The last recognized batter is out of here. 4th one for Cummins.
Almost gets his fifth! A short one and on the body, Southee looks to fend but then awkwardly evades the delivery.
Just wide! Slighly fuller and on off, Southee pushes at it, it goes uppishly just wide of Cummins' hand and falls short of mid off.
FOUR! Excellent picked up! Southee walks right across and this is bowled on the stumps. Southee flicks it in the gap between deep square leg and fine leg for a boundary.
A yorker on off, Santner jams it out.
A short one and on middle, Santner evades it.
Steams in and lands it on off, Santner keeps it out nicely.
This is angled into the middle pole, Santner works it to mid-wicket.
Another short one and on middle, Santner spots it early and ducks under it.

OUT! Another one bites the dust! Once again it is pair of Cummins and Pattinson which is running havoc. Mitchell Santner is walking back now and Australia just the two wickets away from bowling the visitors out. This is another excellent delivery by Pattinson. It is on a length and it threatens to come back in with the angle. Santner defends but does so inside the line as the ball straightens. Kisses the outside edge and goes into the hands of Paine. Third one for Pattinson.

Confusion but safe! That should have been a run out! Southee taps this length ball towards point who is onto the ball quickly. Southee sets off for a run but then hesitates, he eventually goes for it. Lyon picks the ball up and has a shy at the wrong end which is the striker's end and misses. Southee was the one to hesitate so the throw should have been at his end.
One more short ball on the body, Wagner ducks under it.
One more short ball, Wagner ducks under it again.

DROPPED! It went to him quickly but he did get two hands to it so should have hung on. Cummins continues banging it short. Wagner looks to play at it but the ball goes off the glove towards Wade at short leg. He looks to take it with his finger pointing upwards but his hand gets stuck in the grill and by the time he gets them sorted, the ball hits the fingers and pops out.
One more ball angled into the pads, Cummins looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
The batsman defends it from within the crease. End of a nasty over from Cummins.

EDGY FOUR! Between the gully fielder and second slip fielder! Not sure why there is not another slip. Fuller and on middle, Southee looks to drive but it shapes away. It goes off the outside edge and to the third man fence.
On the pads, it is worked towards fine leg for one.
Short and outside off, Wagner ducks under it.
Edged but short! A short one, Wagner looks to pull but is early in the shot. It goes off the bottom edge but lands well short of the keeper.
Fuller and on middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Whizzes past the outside edge! Shorter and outside off, Southee looks to push at it but misses.
Nasty! A short one and on the body, Wagner looks to fend but fails to get on top of the bounce. It hits the glove and rolls towards leg gully.
Uppish but wide! Shorter and around off, Wagner goes after it. It goes uppishly but well wide of gully for one.
Shorter and outside off, Southee looks to put bat on ball but fails to do so.
Another one on the shorter side outside off, Southee looks to cut but misses.
Another short one, Southee guides it towards gully. The fielder misfields but no runs taken.

OUT! Fifer for Cummins! His 5th Test fifer. Excellent effort from the pacer. Proving why he is the number one Test bowler at the moment. It is shorter and outside off, Southee pokes at it away from the body, the ball goes off the outside edge and to the keeper. Just one wicket needed for Australia. Given that they have bowled a shade over 50 overs, a follow-on might be on the cards.
Outside off, Wagner slashes but misses.
FOUR! Off the back of the bat! One more short ball, Wagner is way too early in the pull. The ball hits the back of the bat when he completes his swing and goes over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Back of a length and on off, Santner guides it to point.

In the air... safe! A short one and on middle, Wagner looks to clear the mid-wicket fence. He is once again very early in the pull shot. It goes off the toe-end and lands safe in the extra cover region. Starc overruns it but no runs taken. Maybe if Starc would have gathered the ball properly, there could have been a run out opportunity as Boult had taken off for a run but was sent back.
The batsman goes for the hook but misses the line of the delivery.
On off, it is pushed towards covers.
A short ball outside off, Boult looks to hook but misses.
Oops! A length ball on middle, rises sharply, follows the batsman down the leg side, Boult just plays it with a vertical bat and the ball lobs in the air - but wide of short leg.

Where is the ball? Between the pad and the right thigh. No one knows where the ball is. Full and around leg, Boult looks to flick but misses and gets a thick inside edge onto his pads. Now, Mitchell Starc slips, hence he does not see the ball. Matthew Wade at short leg is searching for the ball. No one behind knows where it is. Eventually, the ball drops down off the pads. Everyone is smiling.
Well played! Gets a long way across, does Boult and flicks this behind square leg for a single.
FOUR! SUBLIME! Full and outside off, Wagner stays leg side of the ball and drives it through the vast vacant real estate through mid off!
A bouncer to to end the over, Wagner ducks.
Boult comes down the track but gets too close to the pitch of the ball. It is hit back to the bowler.
SIX! Boult nails it this time! First of the innings and it comes from the number 11. Boult uses his feet again and swings it high and handsome over the long on fence.
The batsman dances down the track but decides to defend it.

In the gap! Boult once again comes down the track but this time does not get to the pitch of it. He still swings. It goes off the inner half away from the fielder at deep mid-wicket and a run is taken.

Off the glove and goes over first slip! The reverse sweep comes out from Wagner. It goes off the glove and over first slip. It goes towards third man for two. The two batters are enjoying themselves at the moment.
SIX! That is a big hit! These boundaries are not small here but Wagner has cleared one with ease. He comes down the track and swings. He connects brilliantly and it clears the mid-wicket fence.
Good length and outside off, Boult clears his front leg and looks to guide it on the off side but misses.
Shorter and on off, Boult guides it to point. Boult is in serious pain here. His right hand is really giving him some troubles.
One more short one on middle, Boult looks to upper cut it but misses.
Angled into the body again, Boult looks to work it but misses to get hit on the pads.

OUT! KABOOM! There you go, one ball Starc bowls full and on the stumps, he knocks Boult over. Trent moves right across and tries to flick but misses. The ball clips the leg pole. Starc though is appealing as he does not realize that but Boult starts walking back. AUSTRALIA GET A LEAD OF 319!
Starts off with a length ball just outside off, Warner lets it be.
Good length, it starts on off and then moves away. Warner stays back and keeps it out.
On middle, Warner strokes it to mid on.
Lovey delivery! This starts on off and then moves away a long way. Warner looks to defend but is beaten.
Gets this one to angle into the batter, Warner looks to block but it goes off the inner half towards fine leg for one. Australia are underway.

FOUR LEG BYES! Almost got Burns on the first ball again. This starts on middle and then tails back in. Burns looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. It beats the keeper and goes down to the fine leg fence. An appeal from the bowler but nothing from the umpire.
Starts outside off and then gets it to seam back in. Warner keeps it out.
Angled into the pads, it is worked towards mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and around off, Burns pushes it towards cover.
On the fuller side, it tails away nicely. Burns keeps it out.
Outside off, not played at.
Another gentle delivery on the stumps, kept out by Burns.
Three! A low full toss on the pads, Warner works it wide of square leg and takes an easy three.
On the middle pole, Burns defends it nicely.
Angles this away from the right-hander. Burns looks to defend but it goes off the outer half towards gully.
Well bowled! Gets it to tail back in from off. Burns gets his front pad out of the way but by just and works it to mid-wicket.
Still not off the pair is Burns! He gets one on the pads, JB works it to square leg.
Another dot as Burns flicks this to mid-wicket.

NOT OUT! There is an inside edge! New Zealand lose a review quite early. Southee starts this from outside off and then comes back in. It stays a tad low. Warner looks to defend but does so with his bat close to the pad. A huge appeal as Southee feels it is pad first. The umpire shakes his head. Tim really likes it and wants it to be reviewed. Williamson does so. Replays roll in and they show that it is bat first.
Gets it to shape back in from outside off, does not get it in enough to make the batter play.
On the fuller side, Warner strokes it to mid off.
Goes back to bowling length on off, DW keeps it out.
Fuller in length and on off, Warner pushes it to the man at covers.
Fullish again, Warner pushes it firmly to the man at covers.
Burns is off the pair! He pushes at this ball outside off, it goes off the outer half towards gully. The fielder there dives to his right and makes a half-stop. Can't stop the single.
Played that with soft hands! This is on a length and around middle, it moves away. Warner looks to defend with soft hands. It goes off the outer half towards gully.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On the shorter side, Warner hops and keeps it out.
One more ball and outside off, Warner initially looks to play but then tries to leave it. Too late though as the ball hits the bat and rolls on the off side.
Good bowling! After taking a few away, he gets this one to angle back in. Warner realizes that late but does well to get his bat down and keep it out.
A friendly full toss down the leg side, Burns misses his flick.
Outswinger outside off, fuller in length, shouldered arms to.
Full and outside off, watchfully pushed towards cover.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Around off, this is the inswinger, watchfully kept out.
A short ball, pulled through mid-wicket for a single.
This is just outside off, Burns has a poke at it and gets beaten.
Almost chops it on! Shorter in length and around off, Burns pushes it at it away from the body. The ball goes off the inside edge, close past the off pole.
Misfield and a run! Burns pushes it towards cover, Santner misfields and a run is taken.
Outside off, left alone.
One more ball outside off, not played at.
Slightly shorter in length and outside off, Warner slaps it through covers. it is not right off the middle but hit well enough to get two.
Wide outside off, not played at.
One more ball on a length and around off, Burns keeps it out.
Outside off, Burns shoulders arms to this one.
On the fuller side around off, Burns defends it easily.
The batsman works it down the leg side.
On a length again, this is kept out nicely.
Jaffa! Unplayable! This is on a length and around off, it moves away a little. Warner looks to play the original trajectory but gets beaten.
Well played! This is on middle, there is extra bounce. Warner does well to take one hand off the handle and defend it.
Back of a length again, this is guided to the man at point.
Extremely full this time, Warner strokes it to the man at mid off.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg. There is a fielder in the deep so just a single.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On the off pole, blocked.
Good length and on off, it is pushed to the cover fielder.
On off, Warner keeps it out.
On the shorter side, Warner cuts it through point for one.
On the pads, Burns works it to mid-wicket.
On the fuller side, Burns strokes it firmly but back to the bowler.
On the middle stump, Warner keeps it out.
A little too straight, Warner works it through square leg and takes two.
FOUR! Timed beautifully! A half volley but it still has to be put away. Warner creams it through covers and it races away. First boundary of this innings.
Back of a length and on off, defended.

FOUR BYES! No chance for the keeper! Short and on middle, Warner evades it. It keeps moving away after passing the batter. Watling dives to his right, he gets a hand to it but can't stop it from going to the fine leg fence.
Outside off, Warner is tempted to cut but then bails out.
Outside off, it is left alone.
One more ball outside off, it is not played at again.
Shorter and around off, Burns pushes it to covers.
Angles this one into the pads, Burns works it to mid-wicket.
Very full this time and on middle, Burns works it towards fine leg and takes one.
A single to end the session! On the pads, it is worked through backward square leg for one. TEA ON DAY 3, AUSTRALIA LEAD BY 347!
Starts off with a very full ball on off, Warner strokes it to mid off.
Gets it past the diving fielder and gets three! Slightly shorter and around off, Warner guides it past point and the batters run one less than four.
On middle, Burns defends it on the leg side.
Just outside off, left alone.
Lands it on a length and around off, Burns keeps it out nicely.
NO BALL. Wagner oversteps. It is on the pads, Burns looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. It is a massive overstep as well.
He has flicked that off middle. Needed to get bat on ball there. It goes through mid-wicket for one. That swung a long way in.
Fuller and outside off, Burns shoulders arms to this one.
This is on middle, Burns looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads. It rolls on the leg side for one.
On off, Warner keeps it out.
One more delivery on a length, it comes back in a touch. Warner pushes it to the left of the bowler.
Nicely driven but for no runs! Fuller and on off, Warner strokes it but finds mid off.
Good fielding! Full and wide outside off, Warner hits it through covers. The fielder in the deep, Santner, runs to his left, slides and saves one for his side.
A length ball, around leg stump, tucked towards square leg for a single.
On middle and leg, tucked through mid-wicket for a run.

EDGED, THROUGH! FOUR. Full and outside off, swinging away, Warner reaches out to push at it. The moving ball takes the outside edge and goes towards second slip. Tim Southee flings himself full stretch to his left but the ball bounces well in front, beats him and races to the third man fence. The lead is now 362.
Full and outside off, this one does not swing. Watchfully pushed back down the track.
Dropped short, around off, David pulls it through mid-wicket for one.
Full and outside off, Burns looks to defend but the ball swings away and takes the outside edge. Lands just short of gully.
FOUR! Down the leg side, short in length. Warner looks to pull but gets it very fine, just wide of the diving BJ Watling, to the fine leg fence. Moves to 32 from 49 balls.
Full and outside off, pushed through the covers for a single.
Around off, defended solidly.
Landed outside off, Joe guides it towards gully.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, blocked towards mid off.
Landed outside off, swinging away, pushed towards mid off.
On a length around off, coming in with the angle, watchfully blocked out.
50-RUN OPENING STAND UP. Full and outside off, Warner taps it towards cover and takes the single. The wonderful opening combination continues for the hosts.
Outside off, driven towards mid off.
FOUR! BOOM! Fractionally short, around off, Burns swivels and pulls this over mid-wicket! Moves to 11, the lead is now 373.
Lovely ball. Full and around off, swinging in a long way. But Burns is upto it and watchfully plays it towards cover.
Way too wide outside off, left alone. It has been signaled as a wide.
Outside off again but this time a little closer to the off pole than the last one. Left alone again.
On the off pole, Warner taps it towards cover and takes one.
Just outside off, not played at.
Another delivery on a length and around off, blocked.
Extremely full and outside off, Burns strokes it past the diving cover fielder but to mid off.
On the stumps, Burns works it to mid-wicket.
On the shorter side, Warner works it to square leg.
One more short ball but it is down the leg side. Warner looks to help it on its way but misses.
On the shorter side again, Warner stays back and defends it onto the ground.
Another short one, Warner ducks under it.
On the off pole, Warner drops it on the off side and takes one.
A single to end the over! On the pads, it is worked through mid-wicket.
A full toss to begin with, it is eased down to long off for one.
Slower through the air, Warner initially looked to play the slog sweep but then defends it out.
On off, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Comes down the track and then whips it towards wide long on for one.
The batsman has punched the ball off the back foot. They pick up a single.
Flatter and outside off, Warner looks to guide it fine on the off side. Ends up guiding it so fine that it hits the boot of the keeper and then rolls behind towards third man for one.

OUT! CAUGHT! Wagner is amongst the wickets again. Warner falls on the first shot he plays out of aggression. It is short and around middle, Warner makes room and slaps it hard but straight to Blundell at cover. Wagner is delighted. Warner will feel a touch unlucky. He had nailed it but straight to the fielder. Australia are effectively 381 for 1.
Welcomes the new batter with a yorker, Labuschagne gets his bat down in time and works it to short fine leg.
On off, blocked.
Shorter and on middle, it is pulled through square leg for one.
A low full toss on middle, it is worked through mid-wicket for another one.
Slower short one on off, ML works it to mid-wicket.
Landed around off, punched towards point.
Punches this in front of point now, for a single.
Landed around off, no loop, not much revolutions, no pace, bunted back to the bowler.
Short and outside off, cut straight to point.
Arrowed in on off, worked through square leg for a run.

Full and outside off, Burns looks to drive this on the walk but the ball takes the outside edge. A defensive field placement and a lack of self-confidence means that there is no slip. This would have carried. The ball goes to backward point.
Brute of a ball that! It is short and on middle, gets big on Labuschagne. He hops and defends it onto the ground.
One more short ball around off, Labuschagne looks to pull but misses.
Goes full now, ML keeps it out.
Shorter in length and on the body, this is pulled down to fine leg for one.
A huge shout but that seems to be going down with the angle. Replays show that there was an inside edge too. Full and on the pads, Burns looked to flick but missed to get hit on the pads.
A slower short ball outside off, the batter cuts but to point.
This is angled into the pads, Labuschagne works it through square leg for one.
Quicker and on middle, kept out.
On the pads, it is worked to short fine leg.
One more ball on the pads, Burns works it towards short fine leg for one.
On middle, Labuschagne pushes it back towards the bowler.
Another floated delivery on off, ML pushes it down to long off for another run.
WIDE! Way too short and on middle, it goes way over the batter's head. Wided.
Goes very full now, it is the knuckle ball. Labuschagne strokes it through mid off for three.
A short one, it hurries into the batter, Burns mistimes his pull shot towards mid-wicket for one.
This is worked down ti fine leg for one.
Another short ball and on the body, this is pulled through square leg for one.
Looks to bowl the yorker but slips it down the leg side, Burns looks to flick but misses.
Good running! On the pads, this is worked towards deep square leg. It is slightly away from the fielder and two is taken.
Works it with the angle behind square on the leg side. Calls for two and gets two.
Flatter and on off, Labuschagne pushes it to covers.
Tossed up on off, ML strokes it to covers.
Brings out the sweep shot, plays it through backward square leg. The man in the deep makes a lot of ground to his right and keeps it down to three.
On off, blocked.
Flatter and on middle, Burns goes back and blocks it out.
A length ball outside off, Labuschagne gets a long way across and then plays his pull-cum-leave.
And again. Gets across, shoulders arms and then pulls through vacant air.
Smart from Southee but Marnus is prepared. The bowler goes gun barrel straight, expecting the batsman to go across but the Protea stays where he is and flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
Wide outside off, let through.
One more leave outside off to end the over.
Shorter and on middle, Labuschagne pushes it down to long on for one.
Flatter and on off, the batter goes back and keeps it out.
Outside off, Burns pushes it towards cover for one.
On middle, defended.

A direct hit and it could have been interesting! This is pushed to the left of cover and the batters take off. Williamson picks the ball up and has a shy at the keeper's end but misses. Replays show even if he hit, Burns would have been in.
Another single towards cover, this time for Burns.
SIX! All the way! That is some shot. Yes, it is right in the arc but it is a glorious shot. Full and on middle, Burns lofts it straight back over the bowler's head for a biggie.

Nearly chops it on! It goes just over! Length and around off, Burns looks to defend but gets an inside edge. It then hits the pad and then changes directions and goes over the stumps. Lucky escape that.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Slightly fuller and on off, Burns strokes it to covers.
FOUR! Burns might have decided to step on the gas here! Short and outside off, Burns slashes and gets it behind point for a boundary.
On the shorter side, Burns pulls it to mid-wicket. A good over for the hosts.
Full and outside off, driven through the covers for a single.
Landed outside off, pushed straight to cover.
Quicker, flatter and shorter, around off, Burns goes back and punches it straight to point.
Fuller outside off, draws Joe forward, who comes but loosely plays this with an open bat-face towards point.
Bit of revolutions on this one, pitched outside off, pretty full and then turning away. JB reaches out and pushes it to guess where - point again.
A shorter ball to end the over, Burns gets right back to block.
Outside off, left alone.
One more delivery outside off, it is left alone again.
Fuller and on off, it is pushed to mid off.
On the fuller side, Labuschagne pushes it to short cover.
This is angled into the pads, it is worked through mid-wicket for one. 100 up for the Aussies, they lead by 419.
Shorter in length and outside off, evaded.

OUT! He indeed is quite short. For once, Labuschagne gets out for a low score. He works it towards square leg and takes off. Tom Latham picks the ball up and fires it to Santner who collects the ball in front of the stumps and then dislodges the bails behind. An appeal and the umpire takes it upstairs. New Zealand do not seem that excited but they do get excited after watching the replays as it shows that Labuschagne is short. Even the dive does not save him. He walks back disappointed.
Down the leg side, Burns misses the sweep.
Flatter and on off, it is pushed to covers.
Quicker and on middle, Burns goes back to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

Turn and bounce! Australia won't mind this. Santner slows it up and lands it on middle, it pitches and then turns away. Burns looks to defend but it goes off the glove, then hits the shoulder and through the vacant first slip region.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.
On the pads, it is worked down to fine leg for one.
Shortish from around the wicket and on the hips of Smith. He works it wide of leg gully and takes two.
FOUR! Smashed! Flat-batted, a lot like a Tennis forehand. It is short and on middle, Smith clears his front leg and hammers it to the wide long on fence.
Shuffles right across expecting a short one and gets one. He pulls but to leg gully.
One more short one on middle, Smith lets it go.
Another short ball on the body, Smith moves out of the way.
Flatter and on off, it is pushed to covers.
Takes a few steps down the track and hits it down to long on for one.
Smith comes down the track now and works it with the angle to mid-wicket.
Slower through the air outside off, it is pushed through covers for one.
On middle, it is kept out.

OUT! Caught behind! That was a very late decision from the umpire. Shorter and outside off, not far from the off pole. Burns looks to run it down fine but it is a little too close to the ball to play that shot. It brushes the glove and goes into the mitts of the keeper. There is an appeal, Burns stood his ground, the umpire did not raise his finger but eventually did. Maybe Erasmus thought the edge was pretty obvious and Burns would walk but that did not happen. He had to lift his finger in the end. Burns walks back after a start and Santner gets his first.
Goes short straightaway. Smith lets it go over him.
Smith goes for another flat-batted swat. This time though he hits it a lot a squarer then he would have liked. It goes to mid-wicket.
One more short ball on the body, the batter ducks under it.

OUT! TAKEN! 200th TEST WICKET for Wagner and it is of one of the best batters going around. Also, he is the second fastest Kiwi behind Sir Richard Hadlee to get to that milestone. Wagner gets Steven Smith yet again. 4th time in this series. Do we finally have someone who can call Smith his bunny? Well, Wagner may just say that. Once again it is the short ball. Smith looks to pull but ends up miscuing it towards backward square leg. Southee takes a good catch there. Two wickets in quick succession for the visitors.
Looks to bowl a yorker but ends up bowling a full toss. Head plays it out towards mid on.
Fuller and on middle, Head stays back and defends it out.
Outside off, left alone.
This is angled into the batter, Wade blocks it.
This starts outside off, seeing that Wade thinks of leaving it but then it tails back in and Wade defends it at the very end.
Slower one on off, Wade strokes it but finds cover.
Back of a length and on off, Wade keeps it out.
Fullish in length again, this is pushed to the man at mid off.
Outside off, not played at.
On the pads, this is worked towards fine leg for one.
A bumper, Wade ducks under it.
On the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
One more short one on middle, Wade sways away from it nicely.
Uppish but safe! A short one which hurries onto the batter. Wade looks to pull but ends up miscuing it towards fine leg for one.
Wade takes a few steps down the track and squeezes it through gully. Matt Henry, the sub, in the deep, runs to his right, slides and saves a run for his side.
Outside off, not played at.
On middle, it is worked towards mid-wicket. Wade wants a run but is sent back.
Outside off, left alone.
On the middle pole, Head keeps it out.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length around off, it is kept out towards cover for one.
On off, Head stays back and blocks it.
Shorter and on the body, Head works it to backward square leg.
On the body, Head nudges it around the corner and takes one.
Bouncer! The batsman ducks under the bouncer at the last moment.
A full toss to end down the leg side. Wade misses the flick.
This is on middle, it is pushed to mid on.
Good length and outside off, Head strokes it through covers and takes one.
On the shorter side now and on middle, Wade lets it go over him.
Very full and on the pads, it is worked towards fine leg for one.
Shorter and around off, Wade pushes it through covers for one.
Down the leg side, Wade looks to flick but misses.
One more short one and on middle, Head ducks under it.
On the pads, this is worked fine on the leg side for one.
On the shorter side again, it is on the body. Wade fails to move out of the way and gets hit on the elbow. Wade is quite tough as that is a sensitive spot but he shows no signs of pain.
Another bumper, Wade evades it.
On the pads, Wade works it to mid-wicket.
A quick run as this is worked towards mid-wicket.
Outside off, it is left alone.
On middle, it is worked through square leg for one.
Shorter and on off, Head hops and guides it towards gully.
A yorker now on middle, Head jams it out towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Up and over! Short again, Head waits for it and then at the end, upper cuts it over the keeper and to the fine leg fence.
Fuller and on middle, it is driven to mid on.
Full on middle, driven through mid on for a single.
A short ball, down the leg side, Head looks to pull but misses.
A bouncer now, ducked under.
This one holds off the deck, from a length, TH initially looks to pull, with a hop but then adjusts at the last moment, pushing the ball back down the track.
Down the leg side, flick shot missed.
A length ball, down the leg side, Head hops and tucks it past short leg, through square leg for a run.
A length ball, down the leg side, tucked through square leg for a single.
FOUR! Too short and width on offer, it has been put away. Short and outside off, Wade cuts it behind point and it races to the fence.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Short and on middle, Wade pulls it through mid-wicket and bags a couple.
Outside off, not played at.
Outside off, left alone again.
A length ball on middle, Head defends it watchfully.
This one is down the leg side and the batsman leaves it alone.
Very full, around off, almost a yorker, dug out.
Around middle, defended watchfully.
He is giving it his all though. A short ball, banged in the middle of the deck, generating extra bounce, Travis looked to hook but got a top edge which did not carry to fine leg. A run taken.
Full on middle, pushed towards mid on. STUMPS ON DAY 3, AUSTRALIA LEAD BY 456!
A good length around off, coming in with the angle, Head dabs it towards point.
Fuller in length, driven straight back to the bowler.
On the fuller side around off, Head strokes it to covers.

Nicely hit but just for one! Fuller in length and outside off, Head gets it right off the middle. Mid off is slightly deep, it runs to his right and keeps it down to one. So New Zealand are already on the defensive. Australia are underway on Day 4!
Back of a length around off, Wade taps it towards covers and takes one. His first run today.
Cut nicely! Head has come out with an aggressive approach here. He sees this is short and there is width on offer, slashes, gets it behind point and the batters pick two.
